<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-63-0720 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper is a short, informative guide to radioactivity, and includes:-its occurrence, what it is and the use of radioactive substances. Eventsimportant in the complete picture of what radioactivity is, are outlined,together with a description of the three different types of radiation-alpha particles, beta particles and gamma rays. Sources of radiationin Britain, and the average dose per person are given in graphical form.Units to quantify radioactivity and radiation are explained, as wellas where the annual dose of radiation comes from.</TEXT></DOC>